I researched which microcontroller to use. Many builds use Arduino or ESP32. I compared them and learned that Arduino Mega is stable for long LED chains, but is also very large, while ESP32 offers WiFi control at a more compact size. I also learned about level shifting, data line resistors, and capacitors for LED stability. For the software I am going to use WLED for its range of effects, WiFi capability, and ease of use.

